      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values compared against in-vitro measurements at 5 flow-speed combinations. Mean absolute relative error 18.3%; all predictions within ±25% of measured values. Monte Carlo UQ envelopes overlap experimental uncertainty bounds at 4 of 5 operating points."
